</tr> 
<tr> 
<td> <p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.2em; color: #000000; font-weight: 300; text-transform: uppercase;">all things in balance</p> </td> 
</tr> 
</tbody> 
</table> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px;"><a style="color: #008774; text-decoration: none;" href="#author-socialcast-profile">Steve Casale</a>, Pivotal Communications</p>
</div>
<div class="mktEditable" id="letter-from-the-editor-entry" style="padding-right:40px; ">
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;">Extreme events in nature are often responses to things already out of balance—tantrums thrown in part to bring things closer to stasis. The good news is that people generally don't like to let their brothers and sisters linger in their wake for too long. Legions of people responded to help residents sort through the aftermath of catastrophic wildfires in Northern California—one of the latest baroque displays of weather in a year <a href="https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/more-saharan-dust-to-descend-on-capital-as-health-warning-issued-a3660236.html" target="_blank" style="color: #008774; text-decoration: none;">marked by them</a> across the globe.</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;"><br /></p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;">Cloud architects also don't like imbalances that throw things off the rails, or grind down the machinery of business. And the enterprise, eager to reduce workload and operational friction, is rewarding smart tooling and reliability much as it has rewarded app velocity. It might be why a hot topic at <a href="https://youtu.be/1HErHINvyIA" target="_blank" style="color: #008774; text-decoration: none;">recent tech gatherings</a> has been solving the tough nut of actually getting containers into production without friction, on any infrastructure. Salvation currently comes in the form of a runtime container solution: Pivotal, along with Google and VMware, are offering Pivotal Container Services (PKS), to bring predictability and stabilization to ops teams.</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;"><br /></p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;">If you're keen to have the layers of this Russian doll solution explained—the gaps it addresses in running Kubernetes workloads; its goal of consistency across private and public clouds; as a complement to PCF Elastic runtime—Jaime Gonzalez Aguilar's excellent article on PKS in "All Things Product" is for you.<br /><br /></p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;">Roshni Champati accompanies that with a neat article about the Pivotal Knowledge Base in "Labs + Culture"—a cloud knowledge community worth 90,000-plus page views each month. It's a reminder that beyond Day 1, you need more than just tooling to make cloud-native a culture.<br /><br />Finally, the Pivotal event of the year is closer than you think. With more sessions, speakers, and sponsors secured, now is the time to invite customers, the Pivotal faithful, and the software-minded to <a href="https://springoneplatform.io/" target="_blank" style="color: #008774; text-decoration: none;">SpringOne Platform</a>, beginning December 4, in San Francisco. The growing body of stories and cloud journeys, our evolving product strategy, and the changing cloud native ecosystem, will all be part of the conversation.<br /><br /></p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #525e66; font-size: 15px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;">Enjoy.</p>
</div></td>
