</table> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px;">Staff Technical Program Manager, London</p>
</div>
<div class="mktEditable" id="my-name-is-entry" style="">
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00a1e4; margin: 0; font-weight: bold;">At Pivotal I...</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0;">Primarily work with the London Cloud Foundry Product Managers to shorten feedback loops on any of their cross-cutting concerns. I’ve been tasked with deep diving into Data Services to support Ben LaPlanche and Chris Hedley in meeting those needs. My role also entails building touchpoints across our communities to ensure that we share our team learnings and to feed them back into our processes strategically and tactically across the entire program.</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0;"><br /></p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0;">Secondarily, I am a member of the Diversity &amp; Inclusion Global Council, where I work specifically with the team that advises Pivotal’s executive leaders to create a truly diverse and inclusive environment for Pivots</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00a1e4; font-weight: bold;">You can find me…</p> 
<p>In the London office, generally close to a natural light source and with at least 2-3 layers on (sometimes a blanket) as I am pretty much always cold!...practically a reptile.</p> 
<ol></ol> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00a1e4; font-weight: bold;">How I got into tech...&nbsp;</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0;">I’ve always been into tech even though it’s a far cry from what I actually studied. For me, the intersection of tech and humans was deeply intriguing. I think a lot of people decouple technology from the people it is built for and my background in the humanities has always helped to keep me honest about the true point of the software we are designing, which is to make lives better.</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00a1e4; font-weight: bold;">In my spare time...&nbsp;</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0;">I run a video-based blog/vlog at <a href="http://www.chisology.com" target="_blank" style="color: #00a1e4; text-decoration: none;">www.chisology.com</a>. I’ve really been exploring content creation, the nuances of social media and the way this corner of digital media works. I just love creating things and reporting on my experiences.</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #00a1e4; font-weight: bold;">Something you probably don’t know about me…</p> 
<p style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin: 0;">I’m a rider...bicycles, horses, motorcycles... I recently found a lovely Thoroughbred ex-racer just outside of London that I’ll be schooling. It feels amazing to be back in the saddle and training horses again.</p>
</div></td>
